            <section xml:id="d8/d41/classmpx_1_1_mpx_environment_1a6f8ea49742c8e0ac486e396f323cf92b">
                <title>MpxTaskMultiplexer * mpx::MpxEnvironment::_CreateTaskMultiplexer (const char *connStr, bool isWorker)</title> <emphasis>create new task multiplexer</emphasis>
                
<para>this function creates new instance of <link linkend="da/dd3/classmpx_1_1_mpx_task_multiplexer">MpxTaskMultiplexer</link> class. its reference is saved into internal data structure m_tskmpxset, set of task multipexing objects. Access to this set is synchronized to prevent concurrent write operations on it. Every instance of task multiplexer is associated with unique pipe object used to properly terminate its execution. Execution termination is further described in description of <link linkend="da/dd3/classmpx_1_1_mpx_task_multiplexer">MpxTaskMultiplexer</link> class itself</para>

<para>
